The paper discusses the use of Massive MIMO technology in wireless systems, which is a key technology for upcoming 5G systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the reliability and low latency requirements of wireless-controlled robots and cars, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a cylindrical array for measuring channels, which suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses practical implications and insights, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
